# Nifty theme: apply across all views

Follow this theme for every UI implementation so Manager, Associate, and shared components feel like one app.

## Colors (use CSS variables)

- **Primary accent:** `var(--primary)` (~#5B9BD5 blue) – buttons, links, active nav, focus rings
- **Content background:** `var(--background)` – light gray #F5F6FA
- **Cards:** `var(--card)` – white
- **Charts:** `var(--chart-1)` … `var(--chart-8)` – no hardcoded hex; all charts must use theme palette
- **Sidebar:** dark `#232A3B` / `#1a2030`; active state uses primary accent, never `shadow-lg` or `rounded-br-*`

## Layout

- **Sidebar:** Edge-to-edge, flat (no rounded corners, no heavy shadow). Single `main` per page; content area is `div`, not nested `main`.
- **Page padding:** `p-6` everywhere; section gap `space-y-6` or `space-y-8` – be consistent.
- **Separators:** Prefer spacing over `Separator`; use at most 1–2 per page for major breaks.

## Shared elements

- **Page headers:** Use `PageHeader({ title, subtitle })` – same style for Manager and Associate.
- **Sections:** Use `Section` (or `PageSection`) with `title` + children; section titles `text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground`.
- **Formatting:** Use `formatCurrency` and `formatNumber` from `@/lib/utils`.
- **Ranking logic:** Use `topRanking` / `RANK_ORDER` from `@/lib/rankingBadge` or `memberUtils`.

## Cards and components

- White cards, light border, subtle shadow; primary for active tab/toggle states.
- Tables: striped or alternating rows; header slightly darker.
- Badges: success/warning/danger aligned with theme palette.
